node.title: Victoria records 1,073 new local COVID-19 cases and six deaths
node.alt: Cars line up at a COVID testing centre.
node.description: There are now 16,503 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 560 people have died during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,073\u00a0new COVID-19 cases and six\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 16,503\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 560\u00a0people have died during the current Delta outbreak.", "There are 310\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 45\u00a0are in intensive care and 19\u00a0are on a\u00a0ventilator.", "The health department said a further 45\u00a0people were in intensive care but their infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 56,337\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 1,513\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
